				<p id="overview-link" style="float:right;" ><a href="http://spm-v1.dealmakerhelp.com/Default.htm" target="_blank">Overview of Sales Performance Manager</a></p>
					<h2>Purpose of Pipeline Trends</h2>
					<p>Pipeline Trends helps you to understand: </p>
		<ul>
			<li>the flow of opportunities through your pipeline</li>
			<li>the change in value or count of opportunities over the past 90 days</li>
			<li>the trend (in increments of 30 days) from 90 days ago to today </li>
		</ul>
		
		
					<div class="more_info">
					<p>The growth or decline in a pipeline is tracked by each stage so that you see the overall changes in each pipeline stage as well as the overall trend. </p>
		<p>Dealmaker also displays the portion of each pipeline stage that has progressed or regressed during the period.</p>
		<p>Use Pipeline Trends to understand your pipeline velocity, to determine where opportunities are languishing, and to assess your ability to make future sales targets based on these factors and the current state of the pipeline. </p>
		<p>If opportunities that were in the later stages of the pipeline have been won, then your pipeline stages and the activities  undertaken to progress to those stages in the funnel are probably well defined and well executed.  </p>
		<p>If, on the other hand, there are opportunities from the last few stages that have not moved, then it is likely that you should be concerned about these deals.</p>
		<p>It is likely that there is already adequate focus on the latter stages of the pipeline, because they typically contain active and Must Win deals that are closer to closing and are the focus of this particular quarter. </p>
		<p>However, to ensure the future health of your business, early pipeline is just as important in terms of overall pipeline health, managing your sales business, and consistently achieving quota.</p>
		<p>Pipeline Trends shows what happened to the deals in each stage of the pipeline from 90 days ago, organized by Revenue Type, by team or by individual sales person.</p>
				</div>
