					<h2>How to Use Pipeline Trends with your Team</h2>
					 <p>There are three elements to this capability in Dealmaker Sales Performance Manager:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Pipeline Trends</li>
			<li>What Happened to the Pipeline</li>
			<li>Detailed Changes to the Pipeline</li>
		</ul>
		<p>These areas of analysis are explored in the sections that follow.</p>
					<div class="more_info">
					
					<h2>Pipeline Trends</h2>
		<p>Pipeline Trends shows, at a summary level, the development and changes in the pipeline over the past 90 days and the current pipeline value. </p>
		<p>The change in the value in each pipeline stage is displayed graphically in increments of 30 days.  Also, any opportunities that were closed won or lost during the 90 days are aggregated and represented graphically below the line.</p>
		<p><b>Note:</b> If opportunities were created after 90 days ago and were won or lost during the 90 days, these will also be included here.</p>
		<h2>What Happened to the Pipeline</h2>
		<p>The chart in the top right quadrant on the Pipeline Trends screen shows, in aggregate value, the resulting pipeline stage and value for each of the historical opportunities. </p>
		<p>The y-axis is used to separate each of the pipeline stages (in today’s pipeline), and the horizontal stacked bars shows the value of the opportunities today in each stage.</p>
		<p>Clicking on the pipeline timeline links (90 days ago, 60 days ago or 30 days ago) in the Pipeline Trends chart on the left will show the distribution of those opportunities today, displayed by stage. </p>
		<p>You can get more granular in your analysis by clicking an individual pipeline stage in any of the columns in the Pipeline Trends chart to see today’s stage distribution of the opportunities.</p>
		<p>Ideally, a good percentage of the opportunities that were in late stages in pipeline will have moved to Won, and a majority of the opportunities from earlier stages will also have moved forward. </p>
		<p> In some cases you will also see regressions where opportunities have moved back in the pipeline, or where opportunities are lost.  Late stage losses are particularly damaging.</p>
		<h2>Detailed Changes to the Pipeline</h2>
		<p>The matrix beneath the two charts on the Pipeline trends screens shows the detail behind the movement of opportunities through the funnel from 90, 60, or 30 days ago to today.  </p>
		<p>Click the pipeline timeline links (90 days ago, 60 days ago or 30 days ago) in the Pipeline Trends chart on the top left of the screen to scope the analysis  to that timeframe (from then until now).</p>
		<p>On each row, the left-most column shows the starting position for both the value and number of opportunities in that Pipeline stage. </p>
		<p>Moving left to right along the row, Dealmaker shows you where those opportunities are today and it also shows the value change if there has been a change in the value of the opportunities since the start of the period.</p>
		<p>Opportunities are displayed on a green background when they have progressed forward. </p>
		<p>Conversely, when opportunities have regressed they are displayed on a light orange background</p>
		<p>Opportunities that have not moved are displayed on a grey background.</p>
		<p>Clicking any of the numbers in the matrix lists the specific opportunities that make up that number. It shows any changes in Stage, Value, Close Date and Close Probability for each of the deals.</p>
	
					
					</div>
