					<h2>Actions to Consider</h2>
					 <ul>
			<li>Establish a rhythm with each of the sales team – we’d recommend monthly – where you review the progress of deals, and the growth (or otherwise) in the pipeline over the past 90 days. (If your sales cycle is materially shorter than 90 days, then you might select the 60 or 30 day view.)</li>
			<li>In conjunction with the Pipeline Goals in the Pipeline section of Sales Performance Manager, compare total pipeline value and examine any shortfall to goal.</li>
		</ul>
					<div class="more_info">
					<ul><li>Examine carefully any deals that moved backwards – these are displayed on the light orange background in the matrix – so that you can uncover the reasons for the regressions. </li>
			<p>If you have a pattern across the team of deals moving backwards, his is usually an indicator of a poorly defined sales process, poor qualification practices, or an ineffective discovery or customer alignment.  </p>
			<p>If this is not a common problem in the sales team, but is limited to just one or two sellers, then specific execution guidance or coaching is required.</p>
			<li>When opportunities have not moved forward from one stage to the next – you can see these represented in the matrix with a grey background – dig into the detail of the opportunities to determine whether these deals are in trouble.  </li>
			<p>Sales usually go backwards or forwards – they rarely stay the same – and you will to need determine the reasons behind the loss in momentum.</p>
			<li>Check also for opportunities that have moved through the pipeline to Closed Won very quickly.  If these were in the early stages of the pipeline (or did not exist at all) at the start of the period, then there will likely be some cases where either the salesperson is not fully aware of what is going on in the opportunity, or the salesperson is not entering the data into the system too late, or not maintaining it. If keeping the system up to date is the problem, then it is very difficult for the sales manager or sales person to have an outlook on the true value of the pipeline.</li>
		</ul>
					</div>
					<p><a href="javascript:void[0]" class="more_info_link">More...</a></p>
				</div>
			</li>
			
