				<div class="point_text">
					<h2>Best Practice</h2>
					<ul>
			<li>Conduct Pipeline Trends monthly call with each team member</li>
			<p>The purpose of these calls is to determine what can be learned from reviewing the progress of opportunities through the funnel. This process enables the manager and seller to align where deals might be getting stuck, or whether opportunities have in fact truly been lost. </p>
			<p>Develop a plan to determine how to unstick the deals, or clarify whether the opportunity should in fact be removed from the pipeline to give you both a more accurate view of the pipeline value.</p>
		</ul>
		
					<div class="more_info">
					<ul>
			<li>Ask the Salesperson to prepare in advance</li>
			<p>To have a productive meeting, both manager and seller should get into a habit of coming to the call with the requisite information already in hand. It is important that these meetings are focused on improving behavior that will lead to:</p>
			<ul>
				<li> greater pipeline velocity</li>
				<li>an accurate reflection of the potential future business</li>
				<li>a roadmap to building value in subsequent quarters</li>
			</ul>
			<p>Ask the salesperson to review the actual static and regressed deals in particular. The salesperson should try to answer the following questions: </p>
			<ul>
				<li>What is the root cause of the loss in momentum, on a deal-by-deal basis? </li>
				<li>What should have been done differently? </li>
				<li>What changes should be made in the next month to improve funnel velocity or add to the pipeline to increase overall value?</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>
		<ul>
			<li>Use Insights to examine these four key areas:</li>
			<ul>
				<li>Development: What has been the overall value/number change in the pipeline?</li>
				<li>Movement: What opportunities have moved forwards or backwards?</li>
				<li>Value Change: Are opportunities increasing or decreasing in value as they progress through the funnel?</li>
				<li>Won / Lost Deals Analysis: Where stages did Won / Lost deals come from?</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>
